{
  "texts": [
    "On the other hand, scaffolding, a pedagogical approach that involves providing temporary support to learners as they develop new skills, might involve instructors offering sample prompts and clear examples of how to interact with the AI (Jang et al., 2024).",
    "As students become more familiar with the AI tool, these supports can be gradually reduced, encouraging students to take more control of the learning process.",
    "This gradual release of responsibility can encourage students to not become overly dependent on the AI and instead develop the critical thinking and problem-solving skills necessary for independent learners (Darvishi et al., 2024; Tabib & Alrabeei, 2024; Umutlu & Gursoy, 2022).",
    "The integration of AI in education may also vary significantly across different regions, particularly between developed and developing countries (Li, 2023; Pawar & Khose, 2024; Tang et al., 2024).",
    "Developed regions, with more resources and advanced infrastructure, can likely to have greater access to AIdriven educational tools and support systems, facilitating more extensive integration of AI in programming education."
  ]
}